This code is supposed to print `3 10 7` but it prints something else. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

void print3(int a = 0, int b = 10, int c = 0)
{
    std::cout << a << ' ' << b << ' ' << c << '\n';
}

int main()
{
    print3(3, 7);   // intended: a=3, b=10, c=7
    return 0;
}
```
